# C++ Safety Subset

## Must
- Use explicit ownership semantics and RAII for resource lifetimes.
- Prefer bounded/view types over raw buffer arithmetic in new code.
- Keep threading boundaries explicit and annotate shared-state ownership.
- Add invariant checks at module boundaries for schema, IDs, and event ordering.

## Must Not
- Do not introduce raw owning pointers in new core code.
- Do not swallow errors silently in simulation/render/audio critical paths.
- Do not merge concurrency changes without race-safety validation evidence.

## Required Evidence
- Safety-impact note for memory/concurrency changes.
- Test or sanitizer evidence for touched ownership/concurrency paths.
